Unemployment has risen from 4.5 million to 6.7 million in the third quarter of 2019. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Black women are still most affected by unemployment in South Africa. This has been revealed during the announcement of the highest unemployment rate in 11 years. Around 34.5 percent of black women are currently unemployed -- that is three percent is more than black men, who have the second-highest unemployed demographic. READ:Â SA unemployment rate highest in 11 years Black women make up a total of 24 318 477 of the population according to a survey published by StatsSA in July 2019. This is the largest demographic in South Africa. The total unemployment rate has increased to 29.1 percent in the third quarter of this year. The total number of unemployed South Africans is currently at 6,7 million.